In article <Cto1sH.G17@walter.bellcore.com>,
Avi Rubin <rubin@faline.bellcore.com> wrote:
>Is there a way to use PGP to compute the MD-5 digest of an
>arbitrary file without involving any keys or signatures?

Yes.  Use the md5sum program supplied with PGP.  (Or at least, it's
supplied with 2.6ui, it may not be supplied with MIT's 2.6.)

This isn't a sci.crypt question, it's an alt.security.pgp question;
followups redirected.

>not, has anyone implemented a user interface with the following
>functionality?
>
>Enter file name: my.file
>The MD-5 hash of this data is: x87 A6 B2 C9 32 2D etc.

That's exactly what md5sum does.


